tva:Review.tva:FreeTextReview: IM VOTING FOR﻿ OBAMA .
Excellent.﻿
They are people you can﻿ hug.
We love﻿ you to. OBAMA/BIDEN 2012....
Anyone know where I can find the﻿ full video to that speech at :41

I'm Canadian, & I think Americans should stop taking President Obama & his wife for granted. You﻿ really don't understand how much world opinion about the USA changed when he was elected. How much more respected Americans are. I'm white, & I cried when he was elected. I never thought I'd see it in my lifetime. And, I shed a tear tonight listening to Michelle. So, that's from someone on the outside looking in .... look at other world leaders and compare. You are very fortunate to have the Obamas.
Michelle knocked it out of the park tonight! Hope you guys turn around the video﻿ of the speech soon. I want to repost for any friends who missed her.
Obama 2012﻿
Omg an amazing woman ! Bravo ! For both of them ! Obama﻿ 2012 ! Michell obama 2016 ! ! !
Behind every Great Man there's a Great Woman, Michelle you're a model for all women of the world, we love﻿ you From Comoros !
She﻿ is absolutely incredible.
She's a great﻿ example of a mother in chief. I'm proud
go on, Michelle. Go on and keep making﻿ history!
:) michelle we love you and your husband. May God bless and keep﻿ you both and those adorable girls. And in the same way, may God bless and keep the United States of America

As a 25 year old woman who is barely starting out in life and her career she inspires me so much. Tonight when she spoke of her father, growing up with what you had, how her father did everything he could to make sure that she and her brother could go to school reminded﻿ me of my father.... Her and her husband inspire me to be a better human being
I pray the hateful people in our United States takes a few﻿ moments out of their shallow lifes and opens up to what this fantastic woman stands for. Thank you
QQ!﻿
Michelle! From across﻿ the world, you make me even prouder to be an American! Thank you and Mr. President for the hard work in the last 4 years!

Michelle made clear tonight what many of us learned as children. The truth matters; success doesn't count unless you earned it fair & square;﻿ everyone is deserving of respect & many helped those who are successful along the way...the teacher, the janitor who cleaned the school! Shout out to Ms. Banks, Ms. Brock, Ms. Clayman, Ms. Larsen, Ms. Hertz, Ms. Wahab, Ms. Hogue, Ms. Gravely, Ms. Wise, Ms. Conn, Ms. Keener & all my teachers throughout middle school, high school, college and law school!
Lovely! I wish we had a fight obesity program over﻿ here too...
michelle obama is so humble its beautiful... I wish them love and happiness regardless of how the﻿ elections go
best FLOTUS﻿ ever
She makes﻿ me proud to be a Michelle
The greatest President of all time = Obama﻿ !!!
Very touching! Shows how down to earth the Obama's are, contrary to﻿ how they are oftentimes depicted.

Reviewer.Books: The Diary of Anne Frank; Anything by Neepawa, Manitoba's native daughter Margaret Laurence, especially the "Manawaka" series.
Reviewer.Movies: My favourite movie(s) is The Godfather, Parts I and II. I also love The Breakfast Club. Yeah, The Breakfast Club ..... sue me. ________________________________________ TV: The Twilight Zone is probably my favourite TV show of all time. Brilliant morality plays, as relevant today as they were 45 years ago (which is really sad). I watch news and information shows mostly. CBC. CBC Newsworld. The Fifth Estate. Marketplace. Rick Mercer. BBC. PBS. CNN. MSNBC. Dr Oz. The View. The Daily Show. The Colbert Report. Charlie Rose. Frontline. NOVA ..... My favourite sitcom is "The Office." Partly because it helps me take blame off myself for all of the dysfunctional office environments I've been in. Major reason, though, is that it's damn funny. Second favourite is "Family Guy", a crude show, but crudely hilarious. I also watch The Simpsons. The Big Bang Theory. SNL. 48 Hours Mystery. Little Mosque on the Prairie. Rachel Maddow. 60 Minutes. Newsmagazines like 20/20 and Dateline NBC. Some shows on OWN. Also Bill Maher, who is softening on his views about women. He used to be a card-carrying misogynist. But, there is no political comedian I agree more with than Bill Maher ..... Jon Stewart comes a close second ..... I hate to admit it, but I watch Nancy Grace - it's like a car wreck - hard to turn away.
Reviewer.Music: I like mostly singer/songwriters. Joni Mitchell and Neil Young are my favourites.They're both Canadian Prairie kids, like me. Saskatoon's native daughter, Joni Mitchell, is my favourite singer/songwriter with a social conscience. Perhaps not the brilliant songwriter she once was, but she makes up for it in brutal honesty......... I saw Neil Young in concert in Winnipeg in Oct/08. He ripped the place apart, and ended up breaking most of the strings on his guitar. But, Neil Young with a 2-string guitar is better than 95% of them with 6 strings. An unforgettable concert. I also saw Gordon Lightfoot and John Fogerty perform in Winnipeg last year. Both great concerts. John Fogerty is my favourite rock 'n roller of all time, I love the guy ♥﻿ and he didn't disappoint.. I also love listening to great guitar players, as well as the not so great . I, myself, belong in the latter category. One goal I have is to learn to play "The Sultans of Swing" before I die..... and to meet Joni Mitchell. My favourite band is U2 ......My favourite song is "Pride (In the Name of Love)", by U2 ........Favourite album is Joni Mitchell's "Blue" .......... ♫♪ ♫ ♫♪ ♫ ♫♪ ♫ ♫♪ ♫ ♫♪ ♫ ♫♪ ♫♫ ♫♪ ♫ ♫♪
